##Hangzhou Tower Resumes Business, sales hit 11 million in five hours

"Finally! "

The comment was the most liked by the Hangzhou Tower Shopping Mall, a luxury and high-end shopping mall in Hangzhou, Zhejiang Province, after it was announced on its wechat account that it would resume business.

On February 20, the shopping mall of Hangzhou building in Zhejiang Province, which was closed due to the new pneumonia outbreak, officially resumed business. From that day's business situation, consumers finally wait for the opening of the mall mood is by no means a myth.

Although the day's business hours were shortened to five hours from 12 to 5 p.m. , total store sales in Hangzhou Tower topped 11 million yuan, surpassing the 12-hour sales from 10 a.m. to 10 p.m. in the same period last year, according to Hangzhou. com.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Consumers line up at the entrance of a shopping mall to take temperature measurements on the day of the opening of Hangzhou Tower

By the interface fashion comb, as of press time, Hangzhou, the vast majority of commercial complexes have reopened. A search of these stores'back-to-business feeds, however, reveals that consumers'desire to shop is rife in the comments section.

A staff member at the 杭州萬象城店 told interface fashion that since the announcement of the reopening, consumer inquiries have been flowing in and out. For example, many consumers are through the shopping mall wechat public number backstage message consulting shop and counter business. Among the most highly sought-after stores, he said, were fast fashion brand Zara, some beauty and skincare brands and restaurants.

However, he also noted that high levels of inquiry are not the same as high numbers of people. He said that although some customers have come to the store to buy, the overall flow of shoppers in the shopping mall is still small, and even if customers come to the shopping mall, they generally have a clear goal. They buy the goods they want to buy and then leave quickly. There are still some differences from the "shopping" in the past, "after all, this is a very special time, people are more careful, and the restaurants and movie theaters that used to solicit customers were not allowed to have customers. "

A saleswoman at a luxury shoe and shoe counter in Hangzhou Tower made a similar observation to the reporter. She said that the Hangzhou Tower offline shop opening day, where she did not welcome customers into the shop.

But she managed to complete four deals, all of which were directly placed by customers via wechat. She said that fitting clothes, shoes and other products need to stay in the store for a long time, and need to have a lot of additional exposure to goods and people, may still affect some consumers'choices. And now on-line return and exchange goods also convenient, there is protection, so consumers can choose on-line orders. And, in fact, before the outbreak, online shopping had become an important part of their business.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Hangzhou

As interface fashion has previously reported, many fashion brands have tried to launch online sales through wechat groups, live broadcasts, friend groups and other means, due to factors such as the closure of offline shopping malls and the loss of consumer confidence. And as offline stores open, these online channels, which previously focused on sending product information, are also sharing information about how they are doing in order to reach consumers.

"Hangzhou daily" mentioned in the relevant report that the guide of a fashion shop in Hangzhou Tower tried to show the situation of store killing by live broadcast, in the hope of strengthening consumers' confidence to shop offline.

"We still have to try to attract customers to the store, " said the shoe salesman. "The probability of getting a large order is definitely higher if you buy offline and take it with you. "

By contrast, offline traffic and sales for hard luxury brands such as premium watches are close to normal.

In an interview with the Hangzhou website, the sales staff of the Hangzhou building mentioned that "the price of the famous watch is high, customers should still feel more assured on the spot" , and the details of the watch can be communicated through online channels in the early stages, so customers to the store to pay for good goods can leave, you can achieve the shortest stay. On February 20, the highest passenger unit price in Hangzhou building was a single-name watch business, with a turnover of more than 350,000 yuan.

On the whole, of course, it will be a while before the stores return to business as usual, even though business is returning to normal.

On the one hand, the majority of shopping malls are currently open for a shorter period of time, the basic are open at noon, closed in the evening shop closed. At the same time, consumers need to provide Hangzhou City Health Green Code, and through the temperature test to enter the store, more or less will affect the desire of some consumers to go out to the store.

In addition, cinemas, restaurants and other places where people gather are not open, but also affect the overall experience of the shopping center, making the real "shopping" can only be launched at a discount.
